OL,3,CWoman warns millions are going unpaid
OL,4,Cdue to 'emotionally taxing' PIP process
OL,6,FMichael Clarke, from Turn2Us, said:
OL,7,F"We actually think that number could
OL,8,Factually be much higher. We also know
OL,9,Fthat it's very stressful applying for
OL,10,FPIP.
OL,12,F"A very high number of people who are
OL,13,Fturned down for PIP go on to appeal -
OL,14,Fthough the appeal process is very
OL,15,Fstressful in it's own right - (they
OL,16,Fthen) get PIP reinstated for them. So,
OL,17,Fwe know that the process is not
OL,18,Fworking for people who have
OL,19,Fdisabilities as well as it should."
